userInput.ann:label: Probability of Asymptomatic Progression
userInput.ann:description: Proportion of Infectious that are asymptomatic.  Represents the probability an individual in the Exposed state will become Infectious and asymtomatic.

userInput.ann:label: Infectiousness of asympotmatic infections
userInput.ann:description: Infectious without symptoms. Asymptomatic individuals are less likely to infect others or be observed, thus may not be counted and are less likely to receive interventions.
